1
00:00:11,011 --> 00:00:12,388
[theme music playing]

2
00:00:12,471 --> 00:00:13,889
-[vehicles honking]
-[bee buzzing]

3
00:00:15,766 --> 00:00:16,934
KKULBEE EDUCATION

4
00:00:26,402 --> 00:00:27,361
[cat meowing]

5
00:00:52,470 --> 00:00:55,389
{\an8}DAESEONG GOSIWON

6
00:00:55,473 --> 00:00:57,099
-[car door closes]
-[unsettling music playing]

7
00:00:59,810 --> 00:01:01,395
Mr. Kim Ji-uk?

8
00:01:05,065 --> 00:01:05,900
And you are...?

9
00:01:05,983 --> 00:01:09,195
Is Ms. Jung Yu-kyung... your mother?

10
00:01:14,909 --> 00:01:17,369
I think there's been
a bit of a misunderstanding here.

11
00:01:17,703 --> 00:01:19,413
My mom's name is Kim Geum-duk.

12
00:01:20,164 --> 00:01:21,749
And she passed away eight years ago.

13
00:01:24,710 --> 00:01:26,045
Let me put it this way.

14
00:01:27,463 --> 00:01:28,631
[paper flicks]

15
00:01:28,714 --> 00:01:29,799
[sighs]

16
00:01:34,094 --> 00:01:36,263
Mr. Kim Ji-uk, your biological mother

17
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:39,683
is Miss Jung Yu-kyung, isn't that right?

18
00:01:40,476 --> 00:01:42,478
[tense music builds]

19
00:01:43,187 --> 00:01:44,230
Who are you exactly?

20
00:01:45,689 --> 00:01:47,942
In Canada,
a beloved pastor's wife had a child

21
00:01:48,025 --> 00:01:49,151
many years ago, out of wedlock.

22
00:01:49,235 --> 00:01:52,655
What do you think might happen to them
if word of that got out?

23
00:01:57,952 --> 00:01:59,286
You didn't answer my question.

24
00:02:00,329 --> 00:02:01,580
Who I am doesn't matter.

25
00:02:02,248 --> 00:02:03,707
Right now, Kim Ji-uk,

26
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:05,876
what you should ask
is what you can be doing

27
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:08,629
to help protect the reputation of...
this happy family.

28
00:02:13,843 --> 00:02:16,136
I don't know what your game is
or why you're threatening me,

29
00:02:16,220 --> 00:02:17,721
but if blackmail's your living...

30
00:02:18,931 --> 00:02:20,641
I suggest you take up plumbing

31
00:02:21,225 --> 00:02:22,810
because you're terrible at it.

32
00:02:22,893 --> 00:02:24,854
Do you think I care
whether the family of a woman

33
00:02:24,937 --> 00:02:26,230
who abandoned me is happy or not?

34
00:02:29,775 --> 00:02:31,110
I guess we'll see...

35
00:02:31,819 --> 00:02:34,113
if you really mean what you just said.

36
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,162
Why are you doing this?

37
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:44,498
What do you want from me?

38
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:52,715
Kkulbee Education.
We need you to start working there.

39
00:02:52,798 --> 00:02:54,633
[tense music continues]

40
00:02:55,509 --> 00:02:56,510
What?

41
00:02:57,052 --> 00:02:59,054
[Ji-uk] <i>I know that I shouldn't go.</i>

42
00:03:00,973 --> 00:03:02,099
<i>But if I don't...</i>

43
00:03:03,934 --> 00:03:06,896
<i>I won't be able to keep
the promise I made to Grandma.</i>

44
00:03:08,147 --> 00:03:09,315
Why this company?

45
00:03:17,615 --> 00:03:19,116
<i>So I had no other choice.</i>

46
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,452
[Hae-yeong] Oh, hold on.

47
00:03:24,079 --> 00:03:26,290
-[A-reum] Oh! Oh, thank you.
-[Hae-yeong] Mm-hmm.

48
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:29,001
[Yi-lin] New employees,
please gather here!

49
00:03:29,084 --> 00:03:31,003
[soft music playing]

50
00:04:15,673 --> 00:04:17,758
[soft music continues]

51
00:04:22,638 --> 00:04:24,139
You... [gasps]

52
00:04:24,848 --> 00:04:25,808
You...

53
00:04:29,770 --> 00:04:30,771
What are you...

54
00:04:30,854 --> 00:04:34,149
[Ji-uk] <i>I really had... no other choice.</i>

55
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:37,820
I've missed you... ma'am.

56
00:04:55,421 --> 00:04:57,297
[gentle music playing]

57
00:04:57,381 --> 00:05:00,050
Even so... I don't want to worry you.

58
00:05:00,926 --> 00:05:04,138
So, no matter what, Mom,
I'll keep the promise I made.

59
00:05:08,892 --> 00:05:10,227
[Hae-yeong] You... what?

60
00:05:11,186 --> 00:05:12,146
What are you doing here?

61
00:05:13,731 --> 00:05:15,983
It's not what I'm thinking, is it?
It can't be.

62
00:05:16,066 --> 00:05:17,901
[Yi-lin] Hey, you're a new hire, right?

63
00:05:17,985 --> 00:05:19,236
Come to the auditorium, please!

64
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:20,362
Ah, okay.

65
00:05:23,198 --> 00:05:24,116
NEW RECRUIT
KIM JI-UK

66
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:26,702
[comical music playing]

67
00:05:31,415 --> 00:05:32,583
[Yi-lin] Hey, Hae-yeong!

68
00:05:36,462 --> 00:05:37,546
Hae-yeong.

69
00:05:39,256 --> 00:05:40,591
Um, are you busy at all?

70
00:05:41,425 --> 00:05:42,926
-What?
-I need to do the on-site training

71
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:44,053
for the new hires,

72
00:05:44,136 --> 00:05:45,971
but one of the supervisors
went to the hospital.

73
00:05:46,055 --> 00:05:47,222
Hae-yeong.

74
00:05:47,848 --> 00:05:49,600
Please, I really need your help.

75
00:05:50,267 --> 00:05:52,561
Uh, yeah, sure.

76
00:05:52,644 --> 00:05:53,812
[sighs] Thank God.

77
00:05:55,230 --> 00:05:56,273
You know...

78
00:05:57,149 --> 00:05:59,610
that new employee you were talking to...

79
00:05:59,693 --> 00:06:01,153
[suspenseful music playing]

80
00:06:02,154 --> 00:06:05,324
He sort of looks like, um,
he resembles...

81
00:06:07,659 --> 00:06:10,120
your... husband, you know?

82
00:06:10,204 --> 00:06:11,371
Um...

83
00:06:11,455 --> 00:06:13,373
[suspenseful music crescendos]

84
00:06:13,457 --> 00:06:15,459
-My... my husband?
-Yes.

85
00:06:15,709 --> 00:06:17,836
Had I not known
that your husband was in Canada,

86
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,088
I might have said hello!

87
00:06:19,171 --> 00:06:20,964
They really look alike. [chuckles]

88
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:24,468
[guffaws]

89
00:06:25,677 --> 00:06:26,970
Are you serious?

90
00:06:27,054 --> 00:06:28,013
Did you forget?

91
00:06:28,639 --> 00:06:30,224
My husband...

92
00:06:30,307 --> 00:06:32,267
he looks like a model.

93
00:06:32,935 --> 00:06:34,144
[Hae-yeong laughing]

94
00:06:34,937 --> 00:06:37,272
-[chuckles nervously]
-[laughing continues]

95
00:06:37,356 --> 00:06:38,357
{\an8}[Yi-lin] Right.

96
00:06:39,358 --> 00:06:40,359
{\an8}[Hae-yeong] Hmm.

97
00:06:40,943 --> 00:06:42,861
{\an8}-[overlapping chatter]
-[new employee 1] Ji-uk!

98
00:06:42,945 --> 00:06:43,904
{\an8}EPISODE 5

99
00:06:43,987 --> 00:06:45,447
{\an8}-I can absolutely do that.
-[Hae-yeong] Okay, great.

100
00:06:45,531 --> 00:06:46,865
{\an8}WELCOMING THE 23RD COHORT
OF KKULBEE NEW RECRUITS

101
00:06:50,119 --> 00:06:52,538
{\an8}Ji-uk, we're on the same team.

102
00:06:52,621 --> 00:06:53,747
{\an8}[both chuckle softly]

103
00:06:53,831 --> 00:06:55,082
{\an8}Ooh.

104
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:57,501
{\an8}Heard of
"The Buddha of Liter Electronics"?

105
00:06:58,001 --> 00:07:00,087
{\an8}[wooden fish clacking effect]

106
00:07:00,170 --> 00:07:02,131
{\an8}The Buddha was you, Ji-uk? [gasps]

107
00:07:02,214 --> 00:07:04,007
{\an8}So that post was actually real?

108
00:07:04,633 --> 00:07:05,592
{\an8}Buddha?

109
00:07:06,218 --> 00:07:07,928
{\an8}-What post?
-Oh, yeah.

110
00:07:08,011 --> 00:07:10,931
{\an8}Su-a wrote a post
on an online community for jobseekers

111
00:07:11,014 --> 00:07:14,434
{\an8}titled "The Demon and Buddha
of Liter Electronics."

112
00:07:14,518 --> 00:07:15,727
That post totally went viral.

113
00:07:15,811 --> 00:07:16,645
-So good!
-[A-reum] It was so satisfying

114
00:07:16,728 --> 00:07:17,813
even if she made it up.

115
00:07:18,605 --> 00:07:19,481
[both chuckle softly]

116
00:07:19,565 --> 00:07:21,859
She must have embellished
the story a lot. [soft chuckle]

117
00:07:21,942 --> 00:07:23,402
You know
"The Buddha of Liter Electronics"?

118
00:07:23,485 --> 00:07:25,028
-It's this guy.
-[whispers] Stop, stop.

119
00:07:25,112 --> 00:07:26,405
[new employee 1] Yeah, that's him,
he's "the buddha."

120
00:07:27,156 --> 00:07:28,866
-[tapping on microphone]
-Oh, shh, shh.

121
00:07:28,949 --> 00:07:31,368
Now it's my pleasure to introduce
your senior employee mentors

122
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:33,495
who will supervise
your on-the-job training.

123
00:07:33,579 --> 00:07:37,124
A-Team's supervisor
is our newest Team Leader, Son Hae-yeong.

124
00:07:37,207 --> 00:07:39,126
[employees applauding]

125
00:07:47,176 --> 00:07:48,510
[soft grunt]

126
00:07:49,219 --> 00:07:51,555
I'm the Team Leader
for New Business Development.

127
00:07:51,638 --> 00:07:52,973
My name's Son Hae-yeong.

128
00:07:53,056 --> 00:07:55,976
Our newly-formed department
was created to realize,

129
00:07:56,560 --> 00:08:00,564
and commercialize the winning proposal
from our company-wide employee contest.

130
00:08:01,148 --> 00:08:02,399
[mutters] She's really angry.

131
00:08:02,482 --> 00:08:04,401
[intense music playing]

132
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:05,569
Our department's goal...

133
00:08:06,153 --> 00:08:08,906
is to set Kkulbee apart
from the rest of the competition

134
00:08:09,531 --> 00:08:12,534
and to get us to the top,
so mistakes won't be tolerated.

135
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,622
Zero. None.

136
00:08:17,331 --> 00:08:18,999
[Hae-yeong] <i>You son of a bitch.</i>

137
00:08:19,583 --> 00:08:21,168
<i>You come into my company?</i>

138
00:08:21,251 --> 00:08:22,502
<i>Do you have a death wish?</i>

139
00:08:23,170 --> 00:08:24,463
[gulps]

140
00:08:27,341 --> 00:08:29,426
Wow, if looks could kill, I'm so dead.

141
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:32,179
[eerie sting]

142
00:08:32,262 --> 00:08:35,182
KKULBEE EDUCATION

143
00:08:36,391 --> 00:08:38,393
Please board the car
that belongs to your team.

144
00:08:38,477 --> 00:08:39,478
[employees agreeing]

145
00:08:49,154 --> 00:08:50,155
[sighs]

146
00:08:50,239 --> 00:08:52,574
[frantic music playing]

147
00:09:01,917 --> 00:09:03,460
[pants, gasps]

148
00:09:06,463 --> 00:09:08,632
[romantic music playing]

149
00:09:14,846 --> 00:09:15,681
You wanted to talk?

150
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:18,392
You...

151
00:09:25,732 --> 00:09:26,817
[door closes]

152
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:27,818
Hey!

153
00:09:28,860 --> 00:09:30,946
-[grunts]
-[Ji-uk] Let me speak first.

154
00:09:31,029 --> 00:09:33,865
I didn't want this to be how we met again,
but something happened.

155
00:09:33,949 --> 00:09:36,702
The reason why... I can't really get into.

156
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:39,329
But joining Kkulbee wasn't my choice.

157
00:09:39,413 --> 00:09:40,414
[gulps]

158
00:09:41,248 --> 00:09:42,374
Where were you?

159
00:09:43,083 --> 00:09:44,418
Did you go to Canada?

160
00:09:44,501 --> 00:09:46,044
And why didn't you answer your phone?

161
00:09:46,128 --> 00:09:48,422
Do you know how many times
I tried calling?

162
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:50,757
I left you so many messages.

163
00:09:50,841 --> 00:09:52,175
[soft chuckle]

164
00:09:52,259 --> 00:09:54,428
-[gentle music playing]
-What's funny?

165
00:09:55,053 --> 00:09:55,887
You're laughing.

166
00:09:57,514 --> 00:09:59,099
So, did you miss me too, ma'am?

167
00:10:00,726 --> 00:10:02,519
Your first question isn't
why I reappeared,

168
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:04,104
but why I disappeared in the first place.

169
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:07,107
It was just suspicious, all right?

170
00:10:07,190 --> 00:10:10,610
I was wondering
if you somehow ran off with my money.

171
00:10:11,695 --> 00:10:13,447
I didn't go to Canada, and...

172
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:15,032
I did ignore your calls.

173
00:10:16,408 --> 00:10:17,492
Ignored them?

174
00:10:18,327 --> 00:10:19,161
Why?

175
00:10:19,244 --> 00:10:21,621
'Cause I couldn't tell you
what I was doing or where I was.

176
00:10:22,873 --> 00:10:24,249
I didn't wanna lie to you.

177
00:10:25,167 --> 00:10:26,001
You're a liar.

178
00:10:26,585 --> 00:10:28,378
I mean, you and I
weren't even close enough...

179
00:10:29,212 --> 00:10:31,882
for you to have something to hide, right?

180
00:10:33,842 --> 00:10:35,052
Oh...

181
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:38,347
then, uh...
I guess it doesn't matter, does it,

182
00:10:38,430 --> 00:10:40,557
whether I disappear
or answer your calls then?

183
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:43,268
Ah, and that's why you showed up
out of nowhere?

184
00:10:44,019 --> 00:10:47,064
So you don't care either way
if I get in trouble or not?

185
00:10:48,523 --> 00:10:49,858
Do you really think that?

186
00:10:50,442 --> 00:10:51,276
[sighs]

187
00:10:51,818 --> 00:10:52,861
[frustrated groan]

188
00:10:52,944 --> 00:10:54,404
Well, what are we gonna do now?

189
00:10:54,488 --> 00:10:56,656
Someone at the company
is gonna recognize your face.

190
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:57,741
I won't get caught.

191
00:10:58,533 --> 00:11:00,494
They won't remember,
they only saw me at the wedding.

192
00:11:00,577 --> 00:11:02,454
But what if they do?
What if they remember?

193
00:11:02,537 --> 00:11:04,790
So what? [sighs]

194
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:07,751
What should we do?

195
00:11:07,834 --> 00:11:09,086
Um...

196
00:11:09,169 --> 00:11:11,213
[tense music playing]

197
00:11:11,296 --> 00:11:12,422
Listen carefully.

198
00:11:12,506 --> 00:11:14,549
I'll have to hold another ceremony
if you're recognized.

199
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:16,760
And this time, it'll be a real one.

200
00:11:16,843 --> 00:11:18,387
Not like our fake wedding.

201
00:11:18,470 --> 00:11:20,180
[tense music swells]

202
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,015
Your funeral.

203
00:11:22,099 --> 00:11:24,101
[grim music playing]

204
00:11:27,312 --> 00:11:28,271
[exasperated sigh]

205
00:11:32,484 --> 00:11:33,944
[blows air, clears throat]

206
00:11:37,072 --> 00:11:37,906
[door opens]

207
00:11:39,408 --> 00:11:41,952
[tense music playing]

208
00:11:42,035 --> 00:11:42,869
[door closes]

209
00:11:42,953 --> 00:11:44,121
[music fades]

210
00:11:47,874 --> 00:11:49,960
[tragic comical music playing]

211
00:11:50,836 --> 00:11:52,462
[sad meowing effect]

212
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:54,965
[sighs]

213
00:11:58,552 --> 00:11:59,553
[Ha-jun] Hmm.

214
00:12:00,971 --> 00:12:01,847
Here.

215
00:12:03,598 --> 00:12:04,641
Thank you.

216
00:12:08,687 --> 00:12:10,439
Your feelings haven't changed?

217
00:12:10,522 --> 00:12:12,107
[soft music playing]

218
00:12:12,190 --> 00:12:13,024
Huh?

219
00:12:14,109 --> 00:12:14,943
<i>Tteokbokki?</i>

220
00:12:15,527 --> 00:12:16,987
Back in high school,

221
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:19,072
you'd hop the fence at lunch
to go eat <i>tteokbokki.</i>

222
00:12:20,490 --> 00:12:22,951
Yeah, I still... like it.

223
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:26,788
You're not sick of it then?

224
00:12:26,872 --> 00:12:29,624
[chuckles] I don't really
get sick of things that much.

225
00:12:29,708 --> 00:12:31,293
With both people...

226
00:12:32,627 --> 00:12:33,795
and food.

227
00:12:34,421 --> 00:12:35,839
-Writing too?
-Oh, no!

228
00:12:35,922 --> 00:12:38,049
-[music stops]
-I'm totally sick of writing.

229
00:12:41,511 --> 00:12:42,846
-[both chuckle]
-[music continues]

230
00:12:43,555 --> 00:12:44,973
[coughs]

231
00:12:45,432 --> 00:12:48,101
Well... work is work.

232
00:12:48,977 --> 00:12:51,104
If it's work, it doesn't matter
how much you love it.

233
00:12:51,188 --> 00:12:53,190
{\an8}So when you get frustrated, let's go out.

234
00:12:53,273 --> 00:12:54,941
{\an8}I'll buy you <i>tteokbokki</i>
every day you want.

235
00:12:56,443 --> 00:12:58,278
-Really?
-Yeah, nah...

236
00:12:59,696 --> 00:13:02,407
I don't think I could eat it... every day.

237
00:13:02,491 --> 00:13:04,242
How about <i>tonkatsu?</i>

238
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:07,412
Something good happens to me
whenever I eat it.

239
00:13:08,872 --> 00:13:12,542
Something good happens to you
whenever you eat <i>tonkatsu?</i>

240
00:13:13,835 --> 00:13:15,837
[jazz music playing]

241
00:13:20,091 --> 00:13:21,009
GB ELECTRIC

242
00:13:21,092 --> 00:13:22,093
[sighs]

243
00:13:25,096 --> 00:13:26,223
LUNCH, DINNER

244
00:13:26,306 --> 00:13:27,807
TONKATSU

245
00:13:31,478 --> 00:13:33,313
Cancel the executives' dinner.

246
00:13:33,396 --> 00:13:36,358
I'll be eating dinner
in the cafeteria this evening.

247
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:37,609
What?

248
00:13:38,568 --> 00:13:39,528
Yes, sir.

249
00:13:39,611 --> 00:13:42,447
<i>Tonkatsu</i> has been
on the company menu quite often lately.

250
00:13:42,531 --> 00:13:43,615
Is <i>tonkatsu</i> your favorite?

251
00:13:43,698 --> 00:13:44,991
Not especially.

252
00:13:45,075 --> 00:13:46,076
[assistant] Then why eat it, sir?

253
00:13:47,702 --> 00:13:50,163
Whenever I eat <i>tonkatsu</i> in the cafeteria,

254
00:13:50,247 --> 00:13:52,707
then... something good happens.

255
00:13:56,962 --> 00:13:59,005
[dreamy sting]

256
00:13:59,881 --> 00:14:01,925
[jazz music continues]

257
00:14:10,058 --> 00:14:11,476
[chuckles]

