00:39:10,348 --> 00:39:12,309
-[door chimes]
-[sighs]

762
00:39:12,392 --> 00:39:14,394
[pensive music playing]

763
00:39:16,521 --> 00:39:17,397
[Ja-yeon gasps]

764
00:39:18,440 --> 00:39:19,274
Is it bad?

765
00:39:19,900 --> 00:39:21,777
How could Ji-uk not take you
to the hospital after seeing this?

766
00:39:21,860 --> 00:39:23,111
[cat meowing]

767
00:39:23,195 --> 00:39:24,571
How could I show him my bare back?

768
00:39:25,989 --> 00:39:27,532
What if he falls for me after seeing it?

769
00:39:28,700 --> 00:39:30,160
[Hae-yeong chuckles]

770
00:39:31,078 --> 00:39:32,662
-[Ja-yeon sighs]
-[Hae-yeong] Ow.

771
00:39:35,624 --> 00:39:37,542
You can't get mixed up
in things like that.

772
00:39:38,168 --> 00:39:39,878
What if you'd gotten hurt even worse?

773
00:39:39,961 --> 00:39:41,421
He could've killed you.

774
00:39:42,172 --> 00:39:44,966
What if that man holds a grudge
and comes to the house one night?

775
00:39:46,510 --> 00:39:47,803
That's not going to happen.

776
00:39:48,386 --> 00:39:49,596
I'm a company asset.

777
00:39:49,679 --> 00:39:52,766
At the police station,
a company lawyer came to help us.

778
00:39:54,142 --> 00:39:55,602
Is everything really okay?

779
00:39:55,685 --> 00:39:56,770
[sighs]

780
00:39:57,354 --> 00:39:58,855
I'll make sure of it, all right?

781
00:40:00,190 --> 00:40:02,275
Uh, can we keep it a secret
from Hui-seong?

782
00:40:02,359 --> 00:40:03,985
I mean about Ji-uk coming to my company?

783
00:40:04,611 --> 00:40:06,113
Until he's assigned to a branch office.

784
00:40:06,988 --> 00:40:07,906
Why keep it from her?

785
00:40:07,989 --> 00:40:09,533
'Cause if she finds out, she's gonna go,

786
00:40:09,908 --> 00:40:10,909
-"Hey, I knew it..."
-[door opens]

787
00:40:10,992 --> 00:40:13,453
-[Hui-seong] I knew it!
-[comical music playing]

788
00:40:14,079 --> 00:40:15,580
I knew this would happen.

789
00:40:16,081 --> 00:40:17,582
I told you this wedding was a bad idea.

790
00:40:21,711 --> 00:40:23,171
[keyboard keys clacking]

791
00:40:35,684 --> 00:40:36,893
[Hae-yeong] Hmm...

792
00:40:38,353 --> 00:40:39,604
You dated him for ten years,

793
00:40:39,688 --> 00:40:40,981
but you have zero interest
in getting married?

794
00:40:41,565 --> 00:40:42,691
Now you realize?

795
00:40:43,775 --> 00:40:45,819
-Am I a terrible person?
-You're trash.

796
00:40:46,403 --> 00:40:47,445
I mean, feelings can change.

797
00:40:47,529 --> 00:40:48,989
Stinky trash.

798
00:40:50,448 --> 00:40:51,533
So much changes in ten years.

799
00:40:51,616 --> 00:40:53,702
Entire neighborhoods
can be completely redeveloped.

800
00:40:53,785 --> 00:40:55,787
-Ten years ago, I was 22 and...
-23.

801
00:40:57,581 --> 00:40:59,457
22, okay? A kid.

802
00:40:59,541 --> 00:41:01,209
How could I promise to marry someone?

803
00:41:01,293 --> 00:41:02,669
It's too young! Right?

804
00:41:02,752 --> 00:41:03,879
[sighs]

805
00:41:04,296 --> 00:41:06,423
So while that neighborhood
was getting redeveloped,

806
00:41:06,506 --> 00:41:07,757
you forgot how to use your voice?

807
00:41:08,508 --> 00:41:11,261
If you lost interest in marriage,
you should've told him beforehand.

808
00:41:11,344 --> 00:41:13,763
I only realized today
that I don't wanna marry him.

809
00:41:13,847 --> 00:41:14,681
[Hae-yeong scoffs]

810
00:41:16,433 --> 00:41:17,893
Why is marriage always the end goal?

811
00:41:18,643 --> 00:41:21,313
Look, can't the story just end with a...

812
00:41:21,396 --> 00:41:23,315
"Hui-seong and Tae-hyeong
dated happily ever after"?

813
00:41:23,398 --> 00:41:24,274
What's wrong with that?

814
00:41:25,692 --> 00:41:28,195
After ten years,
you're basically husband and wife.

815
00:41:28,778 --> 00:41:30,989
When you break up with him later,
at least pay him alimony.

816
00:41:31,072 --> 00:41:31,948
But I don't wanna break up.

817
00:41:32,532 --> 00:41:33,783
He's my man. I love Tae-hyeong.

818
00:41:33,867 --> 00:41:35,452
Then keep failing those auditions,

819
00:41:35,535 --> 00:41:37,454
-so your man can keep waiting.
-Hey!

820
00:41:39,581 --> 00:41:41,041
-[sighs]
-[Hui-seong clears throat]

821
00:41:41,124 --> 00:41:41,958
Look.

822
00:41:42,334 --> 00:41:43,835
Tae-hyeong told you
he wants to get married

823
00:41:43,919 --> 00:41:45,545
and that he definitely wants children.

824
00:41:45,629 --> 00:41:47,047
If you've robbed him
the chance to have kids

825
00:41:47,130 --> 00:41:50,550
while his sperm's still in its prime,
at least have the decency to break up.

826
00:41:50,634 --> 00:41:53,094
That way, Tae-hyeong will have
the opportunity to have kids

827
00:41:53,178 --> 00:41:55,555
with the youngest sperm
he can shoot out for the rest of his life!

828
00:41:56,223 --> 00:41:58,725
You know how important sperm age is
to the child's health?

829
00:41:59,476 --> 00:42:00,852
You keep talking about his sperm,

830
00:42:00,936 --> 00:42:02,938
but I thought that was something
we weren't supposed to share?

831
00:42:03,521 --> 00:42:04,981
[grumbles, spits]

832
00:42:05,065 --> 00:42:06,066
-[Hae-yeong spitting]
-[Hui-seong laughs]

833
00:42:06,149 --> 00:42:07,609
Ugh, you're gross!

834
00:42:10,695 --> 00:42:12,072
What are you gonna do with that?

835
00:42:12,155 --> 00:42:13,490
[Hui-seong] Tae-hyeong said
it was his wedding present,

836
00:42:13,573 --> 00:42:14,783
so I brought it home.

837
00:42:14,866 --> 00:42:17,160
I'll throw it out. I guess.

838
00:42:17,244 --> 00:42:18,161
[Hui-seong] Throw it out?

839
00:42:18,245 --> 00:42:20,121
Why not just hang it up?
You said you missed him.

840
00:42:21,206 --> 00:42:22,457
Me? When?

841
00:42:22,832 --> 00:42:24,125
When you refill Kitty's bowl.

842
00:42:24,709 --> 00:42:27,045
You complained you don't see
this cat or that damn guy.

843
00:42:27,671 --> 00:42:29,756
Isn't he the guy you were complaining
you never got to see?

844
00:42:29,839 --> 00:42:31,091
Enough!

845
00:42:31,174 --> 00:42:33,218
[playful music playing]

846
00:42:35,512 --> 00:42:36,763
[Hae-yeong sighs]

847
00:42:52,153 --> 00:42:53,196
[door slams]

848
00:42:56,908 --> 00:42:58,910
[sentimental music playing]

849
00:43:11,840 --> 00:43:14,009
[Gi-ho]
Look, it's the noble philanthropist

850
00:43:14,092 --> 00:43:17,470
who's redistributing all his wealth
through fines and settlements.

851
00:43:17,554 --> 00:43:20,557
Are you on your way to the office
or the police station?

852
00:43:21,850 --> 00:43:23,184
To the gym, actually.

853
00:43:24,269 --> 00:43:26,855
[Gyu-hyun] Ah, Ms. Kang.
I was meaning to call you today.

854
00:43:27,605 --> 00:43:29,316
The child abuse case you mentioned.

855
00:43:29,399 --> 00:43:31,401
Let's have legal deal with it.
You take care of it.

856
00:43:31,484 --> 00:43:32,569
Will do, Mr. President.

857
00:43:32,652 --> 00:43:35,947
I'm told our New Biz Dev Leader
and a new hire were responsible.

858
00:43:36,031 --> 00:43:37,615
Keep them on the same team.

859
00:43:37,699 --> 00:43:39,075
This will be good press for us.

860
00:43:41,077 --> 00:43:42,370
What does that matter to you...

861
00:43:42,996 --> 00:43:44,164
the affairs of our employees?

862
00:43:47,417 --> 00:43:49,085
I care more about your affairs.

863
00:43:49,169 --> 00:43:50,795
Shut up and sign here.

864
00:43:53,548 --> 00:43:54,716
[Gyu-hyun sighs]

865
00:43:56,885 --> 00:43:59,054
You two finally getting a divorce?

866
00:44:00,597 --> 00:44:03,516
Well, if I have to decide
whether to live with Mommy or Daddy...

867
00:44:04,351 --> 00:44:06,770
I should probably run away
crying right now.

868
00:44:06,853 --> 00:44:07,687
MEMORANDUM

869
00:44:07,771 --> 00:44:09,189
IF I, BOK GYU-HYUN, AM PUNISHED
FOR DISRUPTING PUBLIC ORDER...

870
00:44:09,272 --> 00:44:10,106
SCANDAL, DAMAGE TO
COMPANY'S REPUTATION...

871
00:44:10,190 --> 00:44:11,024
DISMISSAL,
RENUNCIATION OF INHERITANCE

872
00:44:11,107 --> 00:44:11,941
What is this?

873
00:44:12,025 --> 00:44:13,568
Are you disowning me or something?

874
00:44:13,651 --> 00:44:15,945
Just sign your name and go to the gym
or wherever you're headed.

875
00:44:16,613 --> 00:44:18,198
You really think
I'm stupid enough to sign this?

876
00:44:18,782 --> 00:44:20,575
You can call someone names,
but you can't sign your own?

877
00:44:20,658 --> 00:44:22,160
Are you sure
you can deal with this quietly?

878
00:44:22,243 --> 00:44:23,161
That's not why.

879
00:44:23,244 --> 00:44:24,996
It's because it's my responsibility,

880
00:44:25,080 --> 00:44:27,248
I don't need to sign
some document to prove it.

881
00:44:27,332 --> 00:44:31,169
Ms. Kang, you brought my will
with revisions like I asked?

882
00:44:32,754 --> 00:44:33,838
Yes, I did, sir.

883
00:44:34,798 --> 00:44:37,926
If you don't sign that waiver,
I'm going to sign this new will.

884
00:44:38,009 --> 00:44:39,594
-Father!
-Bok Gyu-hyun!

885
00:44:40,095 --> 00:44:41,554
[tense music playing]

886
00:44:41,638 --> 00:44:43,264
This is me giving you a chance.

887
00:44:43,348 --> 00:44:45,725
It means that while you lack
what it takes to be a business owner,

888
00:44:45,809 --> 00:44:48,436
if you at least have the ability
to deal with a crisis,

889
00:44:48,520 --> 00:44:49,729
I'll make you my successor regardless.

890
00:44:50,355 --> 00:44:52,190
But perhaps it's too big of an opportunity

891
00:44:52,273 --> 00:44:54,776
for a guy who doesn't really understand
what that actually means.

892
00:44:54,859 --> 00:44:57,237
And worse still,
doesn't have the guts to sign his name.

893
00:44:58,321 --> 00:44:59,239
[sighs]

894
00:44:59,322 --> 00:45:01,282
[tense music continues]

895
00:45:07,414 --> 00:45:08,415
All right then.

896
00:45:09,165 --> 00:45:10,125
I'll sign my name.

897
00:45:11,960 --> 00:45:13,086
[Gyu-hyun sighs]

898
00:45:18,466 --> 00:45:19,342
[Jeong-a] One moment.

899
00:45:22,262 --> 00:45:23,972
[tense music swells, fades]

900
00:45:27,016 --> 00:45:29,811
Ms. Kang,
can you please draft another waiver?

901
00:45:30,437 --> 00:45:32,397
Uh... to say what?

902
00:45:33,022 --> 00:45:34,190
"I, Bok Gi-ho, state:

903
00:45:34,774 --> 00:45:37,402
in the event my actions
harm the company's reputation...

904
00:45:39,446 --> 00:45:41,531
I will immediately resign as CEO,

905
00:45:42,031 --> 00:45:43,450
and transfer my assets...

906
00:45:44,617 --> 00:45:46,995
in their entirety to my spouse,
Seon Jeong-a."

907
00:45:47,078 --> 00:45:47,996
Mother?

908
00:45:48,371 --> 00:45:49,205
Jeong-a.

909
00:45:49,289 --> 00:45:51,124
The guts to sign your own name, huh?

910
00:45:51,207 --> 00:45:53,209
[dramatic music playing]

911
00:45:54,043 --> 00:45:55,253
I'd like to see yours as well.

912
00:45:56,504 --> 00:45:58,506
[dramatic music climaxes]

913
00:45:59,966 --> 00:46:00,884
[dog whining effect]

914
00:46:00,967 --> 00:46:02,552
KKULBEE EDUCATION

915
00:46:02,635 --> 00:46:05,221
Hey, Ms. Lee,
how's the research prep been going?

916
00:46:05,305 --> 00:46:07,474
I got the list of directors
for the After School programs

917
00:46:07,557 --> 00:46:09,893
and private schools,
and I am drafting the questionnaire.

918
00:46:09,976 --> 00:46:10,810
Okay.

919
00:46:10,894 --> 00:46:12,145
And you, Mr. Kim?

920
00:46:12,228 --> 00:46:15,440
I only see data on the status
of After School programs in the city.

921
00:46:15,523 --> 00:46:17,484
-And outside Seoul?
-I'm working on it right now.

922
00:46:17,567 --> 00:46:20,695
Grab regional population changes
and the number of two-income houses.

923
00:46:21,404 --> 00:46:22,947
Only for families with one or more kids.

924
00:46:23,031 --> 00:46:23,907
Team Leader...

925
00:46:23,990 --> 00:46:25,742
I'll divvy up the work
once the new hires get here.

926
00:46:25,825 --> 00:46:26,868
Just hold out till then.

927
00:46:26,951 --> 00:46:28,077
[knocking on door]

928
00:46:28,161 --> 00:46:29,204
Look at that!

929
00:46:30,079 --> 00:46:30,997
Hello, everyone!

930
00:46:32,248 --> 00:46:34,250
[tense music rising]

931
00:46:41,132 --> 00:46:42,008
[sighs]

932
00:46:43,593 --> 00:46:44,802
[Asst. Manager Kim] New recruits?

933
00:46:45,470 --> 00:46:46,596
[both] Nice to meet you!

934
00:46:50,141 --> 00:46:51,142
Uh...

935
00:46:53,978 --> 00:46:54,812
Do I know you?

936
00:46:54,896 --> 00:46:56,856
[suspenseful music playing]

937
00:47:01,528 --> 00:47:02,570
[gulps]

938
00:47:03,863 --> 00:47:04,739
[gulps]

939
00:47:05,532 --> 00:47:07,325
If we did, it must've been
somewhere better than here.

940
00:47:08,117 --> 00:47:09,661
Abandon all hope.

941
00:47:09,744 --> 00:47:11,037
Welcome to hell!

942
00:47:11,120 --> 00:47:13,039
-[Asst. Manager Lee cheers]
-[clapping]

943
00:47:13,122 --> 00:47:14,707
[Asst. Manager Lee]
Why don't we do a team dinner tonight?

944
00:47:14,791 --> 00:47:15,625
-Oh! Yes!
-Yes!

945
00:47:16,292 --> 00:47:17,377
-[asst. managers] Dinner!
-Ah...

946
00:47:17,460 --> 00:47:18,878
[both chanting] Dinner! Dinner! Dinner!

947
00:47:18,962 --> 00:47:21,047
Dinner! Dinner! Dinner!

948
00:47:21,130 --> 00:47:23,049
Dinner! Dinner! Dinner!

949
00:47:23,132 --> 00:47:23,967
[Gyu-hyun huffing]

950
00:47:24,050 --> 00:47:26,010
[trainer] Okay, now,
keep your core engaged!

951
00:47:26,094 --> 00:47:27,345
Breathe, breathe.

952
00:47:28,930 --> 00:47:30,682
-Keep your knees apart!
-[clattering effect]

953
00:47:31,099 --> 00:47:32,850
Good, but don't lift your head first.

954
00:47:33,560 --> 00:47:35,019
Okay!

955
00:47:36,437 --> 00:47:37,981
-Come on, you can do it. Up!
-[grunts]

956
00:47:38,982 --> 00:47:40,942
[grunts] I need you to take it! Hurry!

957
00:47:41,025 --> 00:47:42,610
[Gyu-hyun grunts, groans]

958
00:47:44,529 --> 00:47:46,322
[panting]

959
00:47:48,491 --> 00:47:49,534
Gyu-hyun.

960
00:47:50,702 --> 00:47:52,537
You see that client there doing squats?

961
00:47:53,246 --> 00:47:54,747
[trainer]
She has a wedding coming up soon.

962
00:47:55,123 --> 00:47:57,375
Do women try and bulk up
before their wedding?

963
00:47:57,458 --> 00:47:58,751
It's her ex-husband's wedding.

964
00:47:58,835 --> 00:48:00,587
[trainer] He's getting remarried
on a cruise ship,

965
00:48:00,670 --> 00:48:02,714
-and he hasn't been paying child support.
-[woman grunts]

966
00:48:02,797 --> 00:48:05,133
She wants to toss him overboard
on his wedding day.

967
00:48:05,216 --> 00:48:06,050
[grunts]

968
00:48:06,718 --> 00:48:08,052
As for that older gentleman...

969
00:48:08,928 --> 00:48:10,513
his daughter is pregnant.

970
00:48:11,222 --> 00:48:13,516
He started working out
because he wants to be able to lift

971
00:48:13,600 --> 00:48:15,518
his grandkid
until they start elementary school.

972
00:48:16,102 --> 00:48:17,353
[groans]

973
00:48:17,437 --> 00:48:18,813
You should set a goal.

974
00:48:18,896 --> 00:48:20,356
Like becoming stronger.

975
00:48:20,440 --> 00:48:23,901
So that you can lift your girlfriend
in a bridal carry once you're married.

976
00:48:26,070 --> 00:48:26,904
Bridal carry?

977
00:48:29,240 --> 00:48:31,034
Although, it'd be faster
for you to have a girlfriend

978
00:48:31,117 --> 00:48:31,951
who's light as air.

979
00:48:34,162 --> 00:48:35,747
And invisible like air too.

980
00:48:36,873 --> 00:48:39,083
What was that?
What did you just say to me?

981
00:48:39,167 --> 00:48:40,835
[groans, pants]

982
00:48:40,918 --> 00:48:42,170
[detective] As you know,

983
00:48:42,253 --> 00:48:44,672
defamation and libel
are two different crimes,

984
00:48:44,756 --> 00:48:46,758
and libel carries a harsher sentence.

985
00:48:47,842 --> 00:48:49,761
But these comments, they're defamation.

986
00:48:50,803 --> 00:48:52,388
Then he won't go to jail?

987
00:48:52,472 --> 00:48:53,389
No.

988
00:48:55,975 --> 00:48:57,310
Right here. Chapter 51.

989
00:48:58,102 --> 00:48:59,687
He's a real piece of work, this guy, huh?

990
00:48:59,771 --> 00:49:01,397
Insulting your folks.

991
00:49:01,481 --> 00:49:02,815
Okay, what about that comment?

992
00:49:02,899 --> 00:49:04,776
It's libel, but the thing with libel is

993
00:49:04,859 --> 00:49:07,904
the punishment depends on
whether the statement is true,

994
00:49:07,987 --> 00:49:11,616
which is why I contacted you
in order to confirm its veracity directly.

995
00:49:11,699 --> 00:49:12,742
By chance...

996
00:49:13,576 --> 00:49:14,577
is your father...

997
00:49:14,661 --> 00:49:16,746
[somber pensive music playing]

998
00:49:28,716 --> 00:49:29,884
[detective] Thanks for coming.

999
00:49:30,385 --> 00:49:31,386
[Ja-yeon] Uh, I...

1000
00:49:31,469 --> 00:49:33,888
I got an apology letter from him.

1001
00:49:33,971 --> 00:49:35,515
What should I do with it?

1002
00:49:35,598 --> 00:49:37,016
Well, why don't you read it over?

1003
00:49:37,100 --> 00:49:38,601
Then do what you want with it.

1004
00:49:39,435 --> 00:49:41,229
Oh, wow, nice handwriting.

1005
00:49:41,813 --> 00:49:43,648
Did his lawyer write this?

1006
00:49:47,527 --> 00:49:49,362
[Gyu-hyun groans] Yeo Ha-jun.

1007
00:49:50,488 --> 00:49:52,448
I distinctly told him
I'd be at the police station

1008
00:49:52,532 --> 00:49:54,367
to submit a petition. [sucks teeth]

1009
00:49:54,450 --> 00:49:56,119
What's even the point of a secretary?

1010
00:49:56,619 --> 00:49:57,662
[groans]

1011
00:49:58,579 --> 00:49:59,747
Oh, my leg.

1012
00:49:59,831 --> 00:50:00,873
[Gyu-hyun groaning]

1013
00:50:01,833 --> 00:50:03,751
YEONSEO POLICE STATION

1014
00:50:05,962 --> 00:50:07,088
Ms. Yeon, uh...

1015
00:50:10,133 --> 00:50:12,301
[somber music playing]

1016
00:50:12,385 --> 00:50:14,011
[breathes shakily]

1017
00:50:16,848 --> 00:50:17,890
[sighs]

1018
00:50:19,851 --> 00:50:20,977
What do you think you're doing?

1019
00:50:21,060 --> 00:50:22,895
You think by handwriting an apology

1020
00:50:23,479 --> 00:50:25,898
that I'll just forgive you
for sending me a death wish?

1021
00:50:25,982 --> 00:50:27,275
A death wish? You think that...

1022
00:50:32,071 --> 00:50:33,531
My comments weren't that malicious.

1023
00:50:33,614 --> 00:50:34,782
They weren't?

1024
00:50:35,700 --> 00:50:37,201
So you meant for them
to make me feel like shit,

1025
00:50:37,285 --> 00:50:39,078
but not to make me
wanna slit my wrists, is that it?

1026
00:50:39,829 --> 00:50:41,289
And now I get to feel like garbage,

1027
00:50:41,372 --> 00:50:43,624
exactly as you intended,
but I also have to forgive you?

1028
00:50:46,210 --> 00:50:47,587
Don't send me any more letters.

1029
00:50:48,838 --> 00:50:50,965
'Cause I'll never forgive you or settle.

1030
00:50:54,552 --> 00:50:55,470
Do whatever you want.

1031
00:50:59,932 --> 00:51:01,434
I don't need you to forgive me or settle.

1032
00:51:02,143 --> 00:51:03,770
But still, my apology...

1033
00:51:04,395 --> 00:51:05,688
I meant every word.

1034
00:51:06,522 --> 00:51:08,232
I truly regret what I've done...

1035
00:51:08,858 --> 00:51:11,778
and I genuinely... want to apologize.

1036
00:51:13,112 --> 00:51:14,155
"Genuinely"?

1037
00:51:16,032 --> 00:51:18,034
What can I do to make you believe me?

1038
00:51:18,117 --> 00:51:20,119
If there's a way,
whatever it is, I'll do it right now.

1039
00:51:20,203 --> 00:51:21,204
Kill yourself.

1040
00:51:22,872 --> 00:51:24,665
-What?
-I said kill yourself!

1041
00:51:26,584 --> 00:51:27,960
That's going way too far.

1042
00:51:28,628 --> 00:51:31,130
[tearfully] You said that to me
in more than 100 different comments.

1043
00:51:32,048 --> 00:51:34,217
I was forced to think more than 100 times

1044
00:51:34,300 --> 00:51:35,760
about whether I deserved to die or not.

1045
00:51:37,637 --> 00:51:39,096
So now you think about it.

1046
00:51:40,306 --> 00:51:42,058
Whether or not you deserve to die.

1047
00:51:50,983 --> 00:51:51,943
[sighs]

1048
00:51:53,736 --> 00:51:55,446
[somber music continues]

1049
00:52:01,661 --> 00:52:03,704
[vehicle approaching]

1050
00:52:03,788 --> 00:52:05,081
[horn honking]

1051
00:52:06,791 --> 00:52:08,751
-[honking continues]
-[tense music playing]

1052
00:52:09,627 --> 00:52:11,337
[gasps, screams]

1053
00:52:14,090 --> 00:52:16,384
-[yelps]
-[tires screeching]

1054
00:52:20,429 --> 00:52:22,098
[pants]

1055
00:52:22,682 --> 00:52:24,183
[rooster crowing effect]

1056
00:52:26,686 --> 00:52:27,728
-[chicken clucking effect]
-[scoffs]

1057
00:52:32,984 --> 00:52:35,152
[breathing heavily]

1058
00:52:37,530 --> 00:52:39,073
[grim music playing]

1059
00:52:39,156 --> 00:52:40,324
Ms. Yeon!

1060
00:52:41,576 --> 00:52:43,619
[Gyu-hyun panting]

1061
00:52:51,294 --> 00:52:53,045
Ms. Yeon. Ms. Yeon!

1062
00:53:00,344 --> 00:53:02,346
[bold music playing]

1063
00:53:04,807 --> 00:53:07,393
[Gyu-hyun]
<i>Keep your core engaged. Breathe!</i>

1064
00:53:07,476 --> 00:53:08,477
[sharp exhale]

1065
00:53:09,103 --> 00:53:10,229
<i>Keep those knees apart!</i>

1066
00:53:10,313 --> 00:53:11,772
<i>And don't raise your head first!</i>

1067
00:53:11,856 --> 00:53:14,859
[alarm honking effect]

1068
00:53:14,942 --> 00:53:16,027
<i>And up!</i>

1069
00:53:17,904 --> 00:53:19,906
[bold music crescendos]

1070
00:53:36,047 --> 00:53:37,298
KYUNGHYUNG UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

1071
00:53:40,927 --> 00:53:44,138
<i>♪ It was a mistake ♪</i>

1072
00:53:44,221 --> 00:53:47,516
<i>♪ Going out with you ♪</i>

1073
00:53:47,600 --> 00:53:50,311
<i>-♪ You had no interest ♪</i>
-[new employee 1 imitating music beats]

1074
00:53:50,394 --> 00:53:54,565
<i>♪ In this thing called love ♪</i>

1075
00:53:54,649 --> 00:53:57,234
<i>♪ You only needed someone ♪</i>

1076
00:53:57,318 --> 00:54:02,239
<i>♪ Who would do whatever you want ♪</i>

1077
00:54:02,323 --> 00:54:05,326
<i>♪ Someone who only had eyes for you ♪</i>

1078
00:54:05,409 --> 00:54:08,496
<i>♪ Just like me ♪</i>

1079
00:54:08,579 --> 00:54:10,498
<i>-♪ Take me back... ♪</i>
-[grunting]

1080
00:54:10,581 --> 00:54:11,582
[yelps]

1081
00:54:11,666 --> 00:54:15,211
-<i>♪ To before I ever met you ♪</i>
-Hey, bro. Come on. Cheers!

1082
00:54:15,294 --> 00:54:19,256
-Honey, I'm really, really drunk.
-<i>♪ The scar in my heart is too deep ♪</i>

1083
00:54:19,340 --> 00:54:22,969
<i>♪ For me to keep my memories ♪</i>

1084
00:54:23,052 --> 00:54:24,345
<i>♪ I sincerely hope ♪</i>

1085
00:54:24,428 --> 00:54:28,975
<i>♪ That if you find love again ♪</i>

1086
00:54:29,684 --> 00:54:36,357
<i>♪ That person will be just like you ♪</i>

1087
00:54:36,857 --> 00:54:38,109
[automated voice] <i>Cancel.</i>

1088
00:54:38,776 --> 00:54:42,405
<i>You scored 60.
What's important is that you had fun!</i>

1089
00:54:42,488 --> 00:54:44,907
[scatting]

1090
00:54:44,991 --> 00:54:46,951
<i>♪ Take me back ♪</i>

1091
00:54:51,706 --> 00:54:52,581
[sighs]

1092
00:54:54,166 --> 00:54:55,793
[Asst. Manager Lee] Aw, that was great!

1093
00:54:55,876 --> 00:54:57,503
[Asst. Manager Kim clapping]
Yeah, yeah, who's next?

1094
00:54:59,046 --> 00:55:01,173
KARAOKE

1095
00:55:01,257 --> 00:55:04,176
Your team dinners,
do you usually drink this much?

1096
00:55:04,927 --> 00:55:06,178
This is all your fault.

1097
00:55:06,262 --> 00:55:09,473
If I drink, my brain cells
will die faster, and I need them to die,

1098
00:55:09,557 --> 00:55:11,642
so I don't remember
we work at the same company.

1099
00:55:11,726 --> 00:55:12,852
Why are you so anxious?

1100
00:55:12,935 --> 00:55:15,312
No one... has recognized me yet.

1101
00:55:15,396 --> 00:55:16,772
Not yet?

1102
00:55:17,940 --> 00:55:19,191
[groans]

1103
00:55:19,275 --> 00:55:22,862
Except that "yet" means
that it's going to happen eventually.

1104
00:55:22,945 --> 00:55:24,697
[breathes deeply]

1105
00:55:24,780 --> 00:55:28,284
At this rate, maybe it's just better
that everyone finds out.

1106
00:55:28,367 --> 00:55:29,994
Just make it public. I'm fine with it.

1107
00:55:30,870 --> 00:55:33,706
Sure, you'd be fine with it...
but I wouldn't.

1108
00:55:33,789 --> 00:55:35,499
At work, I just wanna be Hae-yeong.

1109
00:55:35,583 --> 00:55:37,126
The New Biz Dev Team Leader.

1110
00:55:37,793 --> 00:55:38,878
You're already the team leader.

1111
00:55:38,961 --> 00:55:40,379
Instead of someone's spouse.

1112
00:55:41,505 --> 00:55:42,631
[sentimental music playing]

1113
00:55:42,715 --> 00:55:44,508
Do you know what'll happen
if we're found out?

1114
00:55:44,592 --> 00:55:47,511
If you eat breakfast at work,
it will make me look incompetent.

1115
00:55:47,595 --> 00:55:50,306
If one day, your pants aren't pressed,
I'll appear inadequate.

1116
00:55:50,389 --> 00:55:52,641
If you make a mistake,
who's incompetent?

1117
00:55:52,725 --> 00:55:53,559
I am.

1118
00:55:54,268 --> 00:55:55,394
[sighs]

1119
00:55:55,770 --> 00:55:59,190
That means you're a ticking time bomb
that could explode any second.

1120
00:55:59,815 --> 00:56:01,317
I'm Team Leader of a key department.

1121
00:56:01,901 --> 00:56:05,112
And I need to produce major results
on this new project, but...

1122
00:56:06,030 --> 00:56:08,157
I'm holding a ticking time bomb.

1123
00:56:08,240 --> 00:56:10,326
[sentimental music continues]

1124
00:56:10,409 --> 00:56:11,786
[Hae-yeong gulping]

1125
00:56:16,082 --> 00:56:16,916
Oh!

1126
00:56:17,958 --> 00:56:18,918
[Asst. Manager Kim] Oh!

1127
00:56:19,001 --> 00:56:21,003
[comical music playing]

1128
00:56:23,964 --> 00:56:26,342
[clock ticking effect]

1129
00:56:28,803 --> 00:56:29,637
What's your name again?

1130
00:56:31,430 --> 00:56:32,848
Kim Ji-uk, remember?

1131
00:56:33,432 --> 00:56:34,767
[Asst. Manager Kim] Ji-uk.

1132
00:56:35,851 --> 00:56:38,229
Our team leader loves things done right.

1133
00:56:38,312 --> 00:56:39,688
Get her in a cab.

1134
00:56:40,272 --> 00:56:41,941
A black luxury cab.

1135
00:56:42,525 --> 00:56:44,693
Team Leader, see you tomorrow!

1136
00:56:44,777 --> 00:56:46,070
-[Hae-yeong] Mm-hmm.
-[Asst. Manager Lee] Bye!

1137
00:56:46,153 --> 00:56:47,279
[Hae-yeong] Bye, you guys!

1138
00:56:47,363 --> 00:56:48,614
Tonight was so fun.

1139
00:56:49,198 --> 00:56:50,908
[Asst. Manager Kim] Wow, you got guns!

1140
00:56:52,409 --> 00:56:53,577
[Asst. Manager Kim retching]

1141
00:56:54,370 --> 00:56:55,579
Ah...

1142
00:56:56,789 --> 00:56:58,082
-Hmm...
-[new employee 1] Let's get you home.

1143
00:56:58,165 --> 00:57:00,501
[pensive music playing]

1144
00:57:16,475 --> 00:57:18,686
Ma'am, I should've thought
how this affected you.

1145
00:57:21,939 --> 00:57:22,982
I'm sorry.

1146
00:57:25,109 --> 00:57:27,653
Regardless of the situation, I, uh...

1147
00:57:28,988 --> 00:57:31,031
I was glad I got to see you again.

1148
00:57:48,132 --> 00:57:50,134
[soft music playing]

1149
00:57:51,594 --> 00:57:53,387
[whispers] Sir, could you drive slowly?

1150
00:58:22,791 --> 00:58:23,792
[grunts]

1151
00:58:25,669 --> 00:58:28,172
No, that's okay.
You should just take this cab back.

1152
00:58:31,842 --> 00:58:33,385
You like things done right, so...

1153
00:58:34,887 --> 00:58:36,222
I'll walk you to your door.

1154
00:58:48,317 --> 00:58:49,235
Whoa.

1155
00:58:50,194 --> 00:58:51,028
What?

1156
00:58:52,238 --> 00:58:53,739
There's someone in front of your house.

1157
00:58:54,323 --> 00:58:55,407
Who is it?

1158
00:58:57,618 --> 00:59:00,329
[Ja-yeon] <i>What if that man holds a grudge
and comes to the house one night?</i>

1159
00:59:01,664 --> 00:59:02,665
[gasps]

1160
00:59:02,748 --> 00:59:05,084
Could it be that guy?
That guy, the child abuser?

1161
00:59:06,001 --> 00:59:08,003
[tense music playing]

1162
00:59:22,476 --> 00:59:23,519
Hey, buddy.

1163
00:59:25,729 --> 00:59:26,981
Hey, sir?

1164
00:59:27,648 --> 00:59:29,066
-Excuse me? Oh!
-[man groans]

1165
00:59:29,149 --> 00:59:30,526
[comical sting]

1166
00:59:31,402 --> 00:59:32,403
Ahn Woo-jae?

1167
00:59:34,738 --> 00:59:35,906
What's he doing here?

1168
00:59:36,490 --> 00:59:39,159
Hey, Woo-jae! Woo-jae, get up.

1169
00:59:39,243 --> 00:59:41,996
-[Woo-jae groans]
-Woo-jae, get up, come on! [grunts]

1170
00:59:42,079 --> 00:59:43,831
[Hae-yeong] Get up, Woo-jae!

1171
00:59:43,914 --> 00:59:45,040
-Hey, Woo-jae!
-[sighs]

1172
00:59:45,374 --> 00:59:47,501
[Woo-jae groaning]

1173
00:59:47,584 --> 00:59:48,711
Move.

1174
00:59:49,336 --> 00:59:50,421
[Hae-yeong grunts]

1175
00:59:52,589 --> 00:59:54,591
[groans]

1176
00:59:55,342 --> 00:59:56,552
[whispers] What are you doing?

1177
00:59:56,635 --> 00:59:59,096
The drunk person's family
should take responsibility.

1178
00:59:59,179 --> 01:00:00,431
Wait, Yi-lin?

1179
01:00:01,932 --> 01:00:03,934
[grunts] Why bother letting Yi-lin know

1180
01:00:04,018 --> 01:00:05,436
when we could just
send him home in a taxi?

1181
01:00:07,396 --> 01:00:09,565
Isn't Yi-lin the one person
who should be informed

1182
01:00:09,648 --> 01:00:10,733
about what's going on here?

1183
01:00:11,483 --> 01:00:14,695
Her husband got drunk and came to the door
of his ex-girlfriend's house,

1184
01:00:14,778 --> 01:00:16,613
a woman who is officially married.

1185
01:00:16,697 --> 01:00:19,325
He showed up here once, okay?
And never before.

1186
01:00:19,408 --> 01:00:22,077
Once becomes twice,
and then soon, twice becomes habit.

1187
01:00:22,453 --> 01:00:25,039
-I'd nip it in the bud...
-He won't remember coming here.

1188
01:00:25,122 --> 01:00:26,915
He never remembers anything
when he's drunk.

1189
01:00:26,999 --> 01:00:28,083
[inhales deeply]

1190
01:00:28,625 --> 01:00:30,002
Why do you keep defending him?

1191
01:00:30,085 --> 01:00:32,004
Look, it's not that.

1192
01:00:32,087 --> 01:00:34,465
I just don't want to be involved
in another couple's drama, okay?

1193
01:00:35,257 --> 01:00:36,467
If what happened tonight causes them to...

1194
01:00:36,550 --> 01:00:38,135
Is it because of Woo-jae?

1195
01:00:38,218 --> 01:00:39,470
Is what?

1196
01:00:39,553 --> 01:00:42,264
The reason why you can't
and won't disclose to the company

1197
01:00:42,348 --> 01:00:43,307
that I'm married to you?

1198
01:00:45,351 --> 01:00:48,604
So, do you mean
that Ahn Woo-jae and I are...

1199
01:00:48,687 --> 01:00:51,440
Are you not over... Ahn Woo-jae?

1200
01:00:53,025 --> 01:00:53,859
That's what you think?

1201
01:00:55,194 --> 01:00:56,236
Yeah.

1202
01:00:56,320 --> 01:00:59,531
[deep breath] I see.

1203
01:01:00,157 --> 01:01:02,785
If that's what you think,
then I guess that's good night.

1204
01:01:05,120 --> 01:01:06,205
I should go?

1205
01:01:07,706 --> 01:01:08,874
With what's happening?

1206
01:01:10,125 --> 01:01:13,837
Whether or not I'm over him...
that's not something I need to explain.

1207
01:01:14,421 --> 01:01:15,506
These are my feelings.

1208
01:01:15,881 --> 01:01:17,091
I'll feel what I feel.

1209
01:01:17,174 --> 01:01:19,176
I don't need your understanding
or your permission.

1210
01:01:20,177 --> 01:01:22,221
It happened to me,
so it's not your problem.

1211
01:01:23,430 --> 01:01:26,517
And I'll deal with it,
so you can leave now, okay?

1212
01:01:27,768 --> 01:01:30,229
[pensive music playing]

1213
01:01:30,312 --> 01:01:31,438
[sharp inhale]

1214
01:01:40,656 --> 01:01:41,782
Hey, Woo-jae, get up.

1215
01:01:42,366 --> 01:01:43,575
Wake up, you bastard.

1216
01:01:43,659 --> 01:01:44,618
[moans]

1217
01:01:44,701 --> 01:01:46,745
Ugh, you stupid idiot.

1218
01:01:47,121 --> 01:01:49,331
If only there weren't cameras around
so I could kill you.

1219
01:01:50,207 --> 01:01:51,333
You're not getting up?

1220
01:01:52,209 --> 01:01:53,293
[grunts]

1221
01:01:53,377 --> 01:01:54,545
-[groans]
-Get up!

1222
01:01:55,546 --> 01:01:56,797
Hey, get up!

1223
01:01:56,880 --> 01:01:58,549
[grunting]

1224
01:02:01,135 --> 01:02:03,262
[gentle music playing]

1225
01:02:06,890 --> 01:02:08,308
[Woo-jae grunts]

1226
01:02:23,323 --> 01:02:24,533
[groans]

1227
01:02:26,243 --> 01:02:27,327
Unbelievable.

1228
01:02:30,289 --> 01:02:31,415
Thank you.

1229
01:02:47,556 --> 01:02:48,474
[both] Good morning.

1230
01:02:48,557 --> 01:02:50,476
Morn... [retches]

1231
01:02:53,896 --> 01:02:55,063
[new employee 1] Good morning...

1232
01:03:00,611 --> 01:03:01,570
[groans]

1233
01:03:02,029 --> 01:03:05,157
Was Son Hae-yeong
always such a heavy drinker?

1234
01:03:05,240 --> 01:03:07,367
[Asst. Manager Kim]
They say the position makes the person.

1235
01:03:07,451 --> 01:03:09,453
She must've lost it
after getting promoted.

1236
01:03:09,536 --> 01:03:10,579
[retches]

1237
01:03:11,455 --> 01:03:12,664
[groans]

1238
01:03:13,874 --> 01:03:14,917
[Asst. Manager Kim groans]

1239
01:03:15,626 --> 01:03:16,919
Just as I thought.

1240
01:03:18,670 --> 01:03:19,671
[sighs]

1241
01:03:19,755 --> 01:03:21,757
[suspicious comical music playing]

1242
01:03:29,223 --> 01:03:30,057
[gate beeps]

1243
01:03:31,934 --> 01:03:34,061
-Team Leader Son.
-Oh, Yi-lin, hey!

1244
01:03:35,187 --> 01:03:36,438
Team Leader...

1245
01:03:37,314 --> 01:03:39,316
I need you to come with me now please.

1246
01:03:41,235 --> 01:03:42,528
What's the matter?

1247
01:03:43,403 --> 01:03:44,488
[Asst. Manager Kim]
All right, these look good.

1248
01:03:44,571 --> 01:03:46,156
Let's move on to the next one then.

1249
01:03:46,698 --> 01:03:48,534
-Great. Next one. All right.
-[new employee 1] Okay.

1250
01:03:48,617 --> 01:03:49,576
[Asst. Manager Kim] That's good.

1251
01:03:49,660 --> 01:03:51,453
[Asst. Manager Lee]
Is Hae-yeong taking today off?

1252
01:03:52,287 --> 01:03:53,664
[Asst. Manager Kim]
This isn't like her. Hmm...

1253
01:03:54,623 --> 01:03:56,124
My calls went to voicemail too.

1254
01:03:56,833 --> 01:04:00,546
Um, hey, Ji-uk, did something happen
to Hae-yeong last night?

1255
01:04:03,298 --> 01:04:05,676
I'll call her again.
She might've slept in.

1256
01:04:05,759 --> 01:04:06,718
[Asst. Manager Kim] Mm.

1257
01:04:11,348 --> 01:04:13,350
Uh, excuse me a sec.

1258
01:04:23,485 --> 01:04:24,736
You don't need to call her.

